    CMDMAIN3 - CMDMAINT REXX ISPF Panel #3

    HRECV01  - HRECV REXX ISPF Panel #1

    HRECV04  - HRECV REXX ISPF Panel #4
    HRECV05  - HRECV REXX ISPF Panel #5

CMDLIST1.text:
)ATTR
  ¢ TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(LOW)  CAPS(OFF)
  # TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(TURQ)
  _ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(HIGH) CAPS(OFF)
  ¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(YELLOW)
  $ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(TURQ)
)BODY EXPAND(||) WIDTH(&ZSCRMAXW)
%|-|¬ISPF Commands Available%|-| +
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD | |%SCROLL ===>_Z   +
¬
+Enter$END+to exit | |#Z   +Commands | | Scroll$UP+or$DOWN +
+
+  Command
+  Name     Description
+|=| +
)MODEL
  #ZCTVERB ¢ZCTDESC
)INIT
  .HELP   = CMDLIST2
  .ZVARS = '(ZSCBR, applid)'
)END

CMDLIST2.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(%+_)
/* %   TYPE(TEXT  ) INTENS(HIGH)                                      */
/* +   TYPE(TEXT  ) INTENS(LOW )                                      */
/* _   TYPE(INPUT ) INTENS(HIGH) CAPS(ON) JUST(LEFT )                 */
   $   TYPE(INPUT ) INTENS(HIGH) CAPS(ON) JUST(LEFT ) PAD(_)
   !   TYPE(INPUT ) INTENS(LOW ) CAPS(ON) JUST(RIGHT) PAD(_)
   ¬   TYPE(TEXT  ) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(YELLOW)
   #   TYPE(TEXT  ) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(TURQ)
   ~   TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(LOW ) CAPS(ON) JUST(LEFT )
)BODY EXPAND(||)
%|-|¬ISPF Command List Help%|-|
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
+  Use the ISPF Command#UP+(usually PF7) to scroll up.
+  Use the ISPF Command#DOWN+(usually PF8) to scroll down.
%
+  Use the ISPF Command#END+or#RETURN+(usually PF3 or PF4) to exit.
%
%
%
%
%
%
%
%
%
%
%
%
%
+Enter#END+command to Exit
%
)INIT
   .CURSOR = &ZCMD
)END

PEEK01.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(%+_)
/* %   TYPE(TEXT  ) INTENS(HIGH)                                      */
/* +   TYPE(TEXT  ) INTENS(LOW )                                      */
/* _   TYPE(INPUT ) INTENS(LOW ) CAPS(ON) JUST(LEFT )                 */
   ¬   TYPE(INPUT ) INTENS(LOW ) CAPS(OFF) JUST(LEFT )
   #   TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(TURQ)
   ~   TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(LOW ) CAPS(OFF) JUST(LEFT )
)BODY EXPAND(||)
%|-| PEEK Symbolic Dataset Substitution |-|
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
%| |Dataset:~word                                 +| |
%
%| |#Symbolic    Value                            +| |
%| |+--------    ---------------------------------+| |
%| |~sym1    +  ¬val1                             +| |
%| |~sym2    +  ¬val2                             +| |
%| |~sym3    +  ¬val3                             +| |
%| |~sym4    +  ¬val4                             +| |
%| |~sym5    +  ¬val5                             +| |
%| |~sym6    +  ¬val6                             +| |
%| |~sym7    +  ¬val7                             +| |
%| |~sym8    +  ¬val8                             +| |
%| |~sym9    +  ¬val9                             +| |
%
%
%
%
%
%
+Enter%END+command to Exit
%
)INIT
   IF (&sym2 = '') .ATTR(val2) = 'TYPE(OUTPUT)'
   IF (&sym3 = '') .ATTR(val3) = 'TYPE(OUTPUT)'
   IF (&sym4 = '') .ATTR(val4) = 'TYPE(OUTPUT)'
   IF (&sym5 = '') .ATTR(val5) = 'TYPE(OUTPUT)'
   IF (&sym6 = '') .ATTR(val6) = 'TYPE(OUTPUT)'
   IF (&sym7 = '') .ATTR(val7) = 'TYPE(OUTPUT)'
   IF (&sym8 = '') .ATTR(val8) = 'TYPE(OUTPUT)'
   IF (&sym9 = '') .ATTR(val9) = 'TYPE(OUTPUT)'
)PROC
   &response = .RESP
   &option   = TRUNC(&ZCMD,'.')
)END

PFKSET01.text:
)ATTR
¢ TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(LOW)  CAPS(OFF)
_ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  CAPS(ON)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH)           COLOR(YELLOW)
# TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH)           COLOR(TURQ)
! TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(LOW )           COLOR(WHITE)
)BODY EXPAND(||)
¬| | List, Delete, or Select PF Key Set | |
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
+Enter#END+command to Exit | | Current PFKs: !PFKSET03+
%
+  SWAP#/+or#S+   PF Key    PF Key
+  DELETE   #D+   Set Name  Set Description
%            -    --------  --------------------------------------------------
)MODEL CLEAR(selopt) ROWS(ALL)
            _Z+  ¢PFKSET01+¢PFKSET02                                          +
)INIT
  .ZVARS  = '(selopt)'
  VGET (PFKSET03 ZAPPLID)
  IF (&PFKSET03 = '') &PFKSET03 = &ZAPPLID
)REINIT
  REFRESH (PFKSET03)
)PROC
   IF (&ZTDSELS = 1) .RESP = 'END'
)END

REXXEPNL.text:
)ATTR
  @ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  CAPS(ON)   JUST(LEFT)
  ! TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(HIGH) CAPS(OFF)  COLOR(TURQ)
  ¢ TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(LOW)  CAPS(OFF)
  ¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(YELLOW)
  # TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(RED) HILITE(USCORE)
  $ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  CAPS(OFF)  COLOR(TURQ)
  % TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH)
  + TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)
)BODY EXPAND(||) WIDTH(&ZSCREENW)
%|-| REXX ERROR Reporting Panel |-|
%COMMAND ===>@ZCMD
¬| | An#ERROR¬has occurred in REXX!erexx   +| |
¬| |Please do a SCREEN PRINT, write down what you were doing, and| |
¬| |then contact Product Support http://mutualnet/is/softools.htm| |
+
$        Error Type:¢etype
$       Error Cause:¢ecause
$                RC:¢erc
$ Error Description:¢emsg

$       Source Line:¢elineno
$   Source reads as:¢sourcel

$Source EXECutes as:¢expandl

$    Stack Contents:¢eresults


+Press%END+to exit
)INIT
)PROC
)END

RHELP01.text:
)ATTR
¢ TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(LOW)  CAPS(OFF)
# TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(TURQ)

~ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(HIGH) CAPS(OFF) PAD(_)

$ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(TURQ)
)BODY EXPAND(||)
%|-|¬REXX Help List Display%|-| +

¬

~Z#rexxname¢Z+ ¢Z+¢rexxdesc

SMPQPNL.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(%+_) FORMAT(MIX)
 # TYPE(TEXT) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(TURQ  )
 ¬ TYPE(TEXT) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(YELLOW)
 ` TYPE(NEF ) PADC(USER) CAPS(ON) JUST(ASIS)
 * TYPE(NT )  SKIP(ON)
)BODY CMD(ZCMD) EXPAND(||) WINDOW(70,13) ASIS
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD

#CSI  Name:`csinm                                       +
#ZONE Name:`zonenm  +
#    Entry:`entry                                                    +
# SubEntry:`subentry                                                 +
#   Filter:`filter1                                                  *
           `filter2                                                  *
           `filter3                                                  *
           `filter4                                                  *
           `filter5                                                  +
+
#ENTER+to continue | |#PF3+to exit+
)INIT
  &ZWINTTL = 'SMP/E Query Panel'
  .CURSOR   = csinm
)PROC
  VER(&csinm,NB,DSNAME)
  VER(&zonenm,NB,EBCDIC)
  VER(&entry,NB,EBCDIC)
  VER(&subentry,NB,EBCDIC)
  &filter = '&filter1&filter2&filter3&filter4&filter5'
)END

SMPQPNL2.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(%+_) FORMAT(MIX)
 $ AREA(DYNAMIC) EXTEND(OFF)  SCROLL(OFF)
 ~ TYPE(DATAIN ) INTENS(LOW ) CAPS(ON) HILITE(USCORE)
 ¢ TYPE(DATAOUT) INTENS(LOW ) COLOR(BLUE  )
 ¬ TYPE(TEXT   ) COLOR(YELLOW)
 # TYPE(TEXT   ) COLOR(TURQ  )
 ` TYPE(NEF    ) PADC(USER) CAPS(ON) JUST(ASIS)
 * TYPE(NT     ) SKIP(ON)
)BODY CMD(ZCMD) EXPAND(||) WINDOW(70,15) ASIS
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
+
| |#CSI  Name :`csinm                                       +      | |
| |#ZONE Name :`zonenm                                            +| |
| |#    Entry :`entry                                             +| |
| |# SubEntry :`subentry                                          +| |
| |#Filter+| |
| |$filter                                                        $| |
+
#ENTER+to continue | | #%PF3+to exit
+
)INIT
  .CURSOR   = csinm
  &ZWINTTL  = 'SMP/E CSI Query Panel'
  &csinm    = ''
  &zonenm   = ''
  &entry    = ''
  &subentry = ''
)PROC
  VER(&csinm,NB,DSNAME)
  VER(&zonenm,NB,EBCDIC)
  VER(&entry,NB,EBCDIC)
  VER(&subentry,NB,EBCDIC)
  &cursor = .CURSOR
  &crspos = .CSRPOS
  &lineno = LVLINE(filter)
)END
